This paper is about natural language inference, which is a subfield of computational linguistics and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural network models, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of syntactic parse information, which is related to the field of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of models for image captioning, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
